CRITICAL VULNERABILITIES (1 Finding)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. NETWORK SECURITY MISCONFIGURATION
   Severity: 9.1 (Critical)
   Original Status: FAILED
   Current Status: ✅ RESOLVED
   
   Remediation Details:
   - Implemented network_security_config.xml with strict HTTPS-only policy
   - Disabled cleartext traffic: cleartextTrafficPermitted="false"
   - Certificate pinning configured for 247tech.net domain
   - SHA-256 pin: 9tXM9TlWKWc+x1ZWP2UjFSjN9vGCxP9a6aD/s3V8XrY=
   
   File Location: android/app/src/main/res/xml/network_security_config.xml

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HIGH VULNERABILITIES (4 Findings)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. HARDCODED SECRETS
   Severity: 7.5 (High)
   Original Status: FAILED
   Current Status: ✅ RESOLVED
   
   Remediation Details:
   - Removed all hardcoded API keys, passwords, and credentials
   - Implemented secure credential storage using Android Keystore
   - Server-side secrets managed via environment variables
   - No sensitive data in source code or version control

3. JAVASCRIPT CORS ENABLED IN WEBVIEW
   Severity: 8.1 (High)
   Original Status: FAILED
   Current Status: ✅ RESOLVED
   
   Remediation Details:
   - Disabled file access from URLs in WebView
   - setAllowFileAccessFromFileURLs(false)
   - setAllowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs(false)
   - Implemented strict domain whitelisting

4. DISABLED SSL CA VALIDATION AND CERTIFICATE PINNING
   Severity: 8.1 (High)
   Original Status: FAILED
   Current Status: ✅ RESOLVED
   
   Remediation Details:
   - SSL CA validation enabled and enforced
   - Certificate pinning implemented via network_security_config.xml
   - Pin expiration set to January 2027
   - TLS 1.2 minimum enforced

5. APPLICATION DEBUGGING
   Severity: 7.7 (High)
   Original Status: FAILED
   Current Status: ✅ RESOLVED
   
   Remediation Details:
   - android:debuggable removed from AndroidManifest.xml
   - Build system handles debuggable flag (false for release builds)
   - ProGuard obfuscation enabled for release builds
   - Debug logging disabled in production

